                <h1>Understanding Hitler's Impact on History</h1>
                <p>Adolf Hitler, the leader of Nazi Germany from 1934 to 1945, orchestrated World War II and the Holocaust, resulting in immense suffering and loss of life. His totalitarian regime emphasized extreme nationalism and anti-Semitism, leading to widespread atrocities and ultimately, his downfall in 1945 as Allied forces defeated Germany.</p>
